text: Port Mòr is a harbor and settlement on the Isle of Muck in the Inner Hebrides off the West Coast of Scotland. It has a population of 27 people. == Fossil evidence == In 2011, a fossil was discovered in Port Mor. It was a bony fish named Moricus in 2015 after Port Mor, where it was discovered. == References == Category:Settlements in Scotland
title: Port Mòr
